[SN]TITLE[SN]
Four bailed over child sexual exploitation in Bristol area

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four men arrested on suspicion of sexually exploiting children in the Bristol area between 2011 and 2012, have been released on bail.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The men, all in their 20s, were arrested on Wednesday after warrants were executed at four Bristol addresses and a location in Newport, South Wales.
The three alleged victims were all aged between 12 and 15 at the time.
Avon and Somerset Police said all four men have now been released on bail pending further enquiries.
